WEBVTT

00:00.227 --> 00:02.544
<i>Kenny: This is the house
where my family lives.</i>

00:02.694 --> 00:04.689
<i>Yesterday we were perfect.</i>

00:04.928 --> 00:08.023
<i>The O'Neals were
wholesome, well-respected,</i>

00:08.058 --> 00:11.559
<i>religious... the face
of St. Barklay's Parish.</i>

00:11.595 --> 00:12.927
<i>Literally.</i>

00:12.963 --> 00:14.763
<i>But then last night happened.</i>

00:14.798 --> 00:16.998
I'm gay, Mom.

00:17.034 --> 00:19.034
What?

00:19.069 --> 00:20.535
[Creaking]

00:21.638 --> 00:23.605
I think Kenny said he's gay.

00:23.640 --> 00:24.839
Twice.

00:24.875 --> 00:26.574
And it also sounds like
you're getting a divorce.

00:26.610 --> 00:28.810
Unfortunately, the acoustics
in here are amazing.

00:28.845 --> 00:31.813
<i>Oh, and as it turns out,</i>

00:31.848 --> 00:34.783
<i>my sister is a thief and
my brother's not eating.</i>

00:34.818 --> 00:37.318
<i>Who knows what life
will be like for us now?</i>

00:44.661 --> 00:46.461
What the...

00:46.496 --> 00:48.096
Kenny!

00:50.067 --> 00:51.699
There's no one left to wrestle,

00:51.735 --> 00:53.234
so I'm wrestling my demons.

00:53.270 --> 00:56.471
Whoa! No! No! Aah!

00:56.506 --> 00:57.506
Jim...

00:57.541 --> 00:59.274
- [Glass shatters]
- Aah!

00:59.309 --> 01:00.675
[Helicopter blades whirring]

01:00.710 --> 01:02.577
Oh.

01:04.013 --> 01:05.180
I stole it from Dad,

01:05.215 --> 01:07.315
but I forgot to steal the bullets.

01:10.387 --> 01:12.754
Hey... Mom.

01:12.789 --> 01:14.622
I'd give you a hug, but
I don't have any arms.

01:14.658 --> 01:15.957
Also, you're gay.

01:15.992 --> 01:19.060
Uh, ma, you're bleeding
all over the rug.

01:19.096 --> 01:20.228
I'm fine.

01:20.263 --> 01:21.863
Your father's roasting
vermin for dinner.

01:22.833 --> 01:24.299
I'd have given my right arm

01:24.334 --> 01:26.367
to see your father
cook before the divorce.

01:26.436 --> 01:28.303
Oh, and one more bit of bad news, Kenny.

01:28.338 --> 01:29.270
Because of our sins,

01:29.306 --> 01:30.972
they canceled "Jimmy Kimmel Live!"

01:31.007 --> 01:32.207
What?!

01:32.242 --> 01:34.309
Now I have to get a real job.

01:34.344 --> 01:37.946
What takes like an hour a day
and pays a billion dollars?

01:37.981 --> 01:40.882
Wha... nooooo!

01:42.219 --> 01:43.585
[Birds chirping]

01:43.620 --> 01:44.853
Morning.

01:44.888 --> 01:46.721
Hey! Morning, Kenny.

01:46.756 --> 01:47.922
How is everybody?

01:47.958 --> 01:50.125
Pretty fantastic.

01:54.297 --> 01:56.097
What is happening?

01:56.133 --> 01:57.732
Mom's over-performing domesticity

01:57.767 --> 02:00.335
in a misguided attempt to
avoid our family's new reality.

02:00.370 --> 02:02.237
And she's making pancakes.

02:03.573 --> 02:05.473
I don't know what's more disturbing...

02:05.509 --> 02:07.709
Bloody stumps and
vermin or this breakfast.

02:07.744 --> 02:08.744
Oh, this.

02:08.777 --> 02:10.178
This is definitely more disturbing.

02:10.213 --> 02:12.046
You're always right, Jimmy Kimmel.

02:12.240 --> 02:16.228
Synced and corrected by VitoSilans
- www.Addic7ed.com -

02:17.821 --> 02:18.820
- Mmm. Thank you.
- You're welcome.

02:18.855 --> 02:20.522
Mom, these pancakes are amazing.

02:20.557 --> 02:21.856
- Oh, thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

02:21.892 --> 02:24.425
Uh, so, are we gonna
talk about what happened?

02:24.461 --> 02:25.627
Sure. Your father and I

02:25.662 --> 02:27.529
discussed the situation last night,

02:27.564 --> 02:30.131
and we are on the exact
same page about everything.

02:30.167 --> 02:31.432
You completely went against our plan.

02:31.468 --> 02:32.500
We were gonna wait until the kids

02:32.536 --> 02:33.936
were in college before we split up.

02:33.937 --> 02:35.770
Oh, and keep up a lie so everyone
could think we're perfect?

02:35.805 --> 02:37.505
I am not ashamed that
I finally spoke up.

02:37.541 --> 02:39.941
And now we're getting a divorce
and sleeping in the same bed.

02:39.976 --> 02:42.010
This is so like you.

02:42.045 --> 02:43.444
You never think things through.

02:43.480 --> 02:44.646
Ah.

02:44.681 --> 02:45.713
You don't need three pillows.

02:45.749 --> 02:46.915
My elbows rub.

02:46.950 --> 02:49.417
So after a restful night's sleep,

02:49.452 --> 02:51.152
I came up with a plan.

02:51.188 --> 02:52.654
I have a plan, too.

02:52.689 --> 02:54.923
- Oh, really?
- Uh-huh.

02:54.958 --> 02:58.760
I mean, I don't need it
written on a little list, but...

02:58.795 --> 03:00.461
It's up here.

03:00.497 --> 03:02.263
It's a brain plan.

03:02.299 --> 03:05.533
That's made up. Here's
how a real plan works.

03:05.569 --> 03:07.969
First, I made Jimmy pancakes
in the shape of Jesus

03:08.004 --> 03:10.605
to encourage him to eat and
get over his male anorexia.

03:10.640 --> 03:13.408
And it worked. This is my fourth Jesus.

03:13.443 --> 03:14.776
- Ha ha.
- Great.

03:14.811 --> 03:16.011
We can cross that off the list.

03:16.046 --> 03:18.112
Next, your father and Jimmy

03:18.148 --> 03:20.348
are gonna go sell that car
Shannon illegally bought

03:20.383 --> 03:22.483
with the money she raised
for poor African children.

03:22.519 --> 03:23.818
Thanks, guys. That
really frees up my day.

03:23.853 --> 03:26.554
Oh, no, young lady. You
do not have a "free day."

03:26.590 --> 03:28.489
You have your science fair today,

03:28.525 --> 03:30.792
which we will attend as a family

03:30.827 --> 03:32.627
in perfectly pressed shirts

03:32.662 --> 03:34.362
so we can watch you win first prize

03:34.397 --> 03:36.197
and put this public shaming behind us.

03:36.233 --> 03:38.258
And that is how you make a plan.

03:38.283 --> 03:39.334
[Pen clicks]

03:39.369 --> 03:41.603
Um, okay. Well, actually,

03:41.638 --> 03:42.904
I think you're forgetting

03:42.939 --> 03:44.839
a couple of pretty important things.

03:44.874 --> 03:46.040
Oh?

03:46.076 --> 03:48.109
Like my thing from last night?

03:48.144 --> 03:51.045
Oh. You still have that?

03:51.081 --> 03:52.280
Kenny.

03:52.315 --> 03:53.381
[Pen clicks]

03:53.416 --> 03:54.416
TBD.

03:54.417 --> 03:55.417
What? No. It's not TBD.

03:55.418 --> 03:57.151
It's "D". It's way "D"!

03:57.187 --> 03:59.520
- Well, I thought it was LGBT.
- No, just look.

03:59.556 --> 04:00.888
I know this is hard for you

04:00.924 --> 04:03.024
because it means we're
not perfect anymore.

04:03.059 --> 04:05.627
But there's no sense
in trying to hide it.

04:05.662 --> 04:07.495
- I'm gay and everyone knows it!
- [Sighs]

04:07.530 --> 04:08.730
Hey, O'Neals.

04:08.765 --> 04:10.465
Sorry I didn't say goodbye last night.

04:10.500 --> 04:11.633
I had to leave early,

04:11.668 --> 04:13.308
and then I dropped my
phone in the toilet.

04:14.704 --> 04:15.737
Did I miss anything?

04:15.772 --> 04:17.372
Nope.

04:17.406 --> 04:19.339
[Chuckles nervously] Not a thing.

04:19.375 --> 04:21.375
Giiiiirl.

04:21.411 --> 04:24.112
Mnh-mnh.

04:24.147 --> 04:25.346
Mnh-mnh.

04:26.616 --> 04:28.816
[Sighs] Look, Kenny. I know it's hard,

04:28.852 --> 04:31.085
but you got to break
up with Mimi like a man.

04:31.121 --> 04:32.186
Even though you're gay.

04:33.390 --> 04:36.324
Not that gay people aren't men.

04:37.827 --> 04:38.827
Here's a joke.

04:38.862 --> 04:40.895
What do gay horses eat?

04:40.930 --> 04:42.330
[Clears throat]

04:42.365 --> 04:43.725
You can go sell that car now, Dad.

04:43.733 --> 04:44.733
Thank you.

04:44.768 --> 04:46.601
Dad, I really liked your joke.

04:46.636 --> 04:47.835
Hey. Sorry, Mimi.

04:47.871 --> 04:49.837
Uh, Mimi, I have something to tell you.

04:49.873 --> 04:53.708
Shannon, why don't you show
Mimi your science project?

04:53.743 --> 04:55.243
She made an erupting volcano.

04:55.278 --> 04:58.046
Actually, I haven't done it yet.

04:58.081 --> 04:59.380
What?!

04:59.416 --> 05:01.616
But your volcano is
gonna win the blue ribbon,

05:01.651 --> 05:03.751
and we are gonna take a
picture with it as a family.

05:03.787 --> 05:05.119
It's on my list!

05:05.155 --> 05:06.587
But everyone does a volcano.

05:06.623 --> 05:07.722
It's, like, so expected.

05:07.757 --> 05:09.424
Like, I don't know, a Catholic mom

05:09.459 --> 05:11.259
forcing her son to pretend he's not...

05:11.294 --> 05:12.860
Volcano!

05:12.896 --> 05:16.297
Or something. Now.

05:16.333 --> 05:18.933
Whatever it is, you can tell me.

05:18.968 --> 05:21.436
All right, well, you know how
I was right about your bangs?

05:21.471 --> 05:22.637
Uh-huh.

05:22.672 --> 05:25.239
They just frame your face so perfectly.

05:25.275 --> 05:26.074
Mm-hmm.

05:26.109 --> 05:27.742
- [Gasps]
- Oh, my gosh!

05:27.777 --> 05:29.811
Mimi, I'm so sorry.

05:29.846 --> 05:32.580
I...Tripped.

05:32.615 --> 05:36.451
Why don't you go upstairs
and get cleaned off

05:36.486 --> 05:38.219
before my heterosexual son

05:38.254 --> 05:40.254
thinks this is [Chuckling]
a wet t-shirt contest?

05:40.290 --> 05:41.322
- [Laughs]
- Okay.

05:41.358 --> 05:42.690
I got some in my eye.

05:42.726 --> 05:43.726
Yeah. Oh, I'm sorry.

05:43.727 --> 05:44.759
It really burns.

05:44.794 --> 05:46.594
Yeah, go on ahead there, hon.

05:46.629 --> 05:48.796
- Ow!
- Okay.

05:48.832 --> 05:50.198
Just take your time there, honey!

05:50.233 --> 05:51.933
You cannot keep me from
telling Mimi forever!

05:51.968 --> 05:55.103
How do you even know you
are what you say you are?

05:55.138 --> 05:56.270
You're still just a kid.

05:56.306 --> 05:58.406
You've never even had
relations with a girl.

05:58.441 --> 05:59.874
It's like when you were little

05:59.909 --> 06:01.376
and you said you hated papaya,

06:01.444 --> 06:02.810
but you hadn't even tried it.

06:02.846 --> 06:05.480
Then once you tried it,
you couldn't get enough.

06:07.144 --> 06:08.149
Hi.

06:08.184 --> 06:09.617
Oh.

06:09.652 --> 06:11.052
How are you guys?

06:11.087 --> 06:12.587
Well, my mom doesn't think I'm gay,

06:12.622 --> 06:14.255
and she wants me to try Mimi's papaya.

06:14.290 --> 06:15.590
Yeah.

06:15.625 --> 06:17.592
Eileen, the good news is,
the community is behind you.

06:17.627 --> 06:19.527
I ran into Kelly Butler
at the grocery store.

06:19.562 --> 06:21.362
She didn't want to
stop by and bother you,

06:21.398 --> 06:23.030
but she told me to give you this ham.

06:23.066 --> 06:25.366
Pity pork.

06:25.402 --> 06:27.268
Do you see how far we've fallen, Kenny?

06:27.303 --> 06:29.237
Yeah, you know, 'cause
that's what people send

06:29.272 --> 06:30.838
when you've had a gay in the family.

06:30.874 --> 06:33.708
♪ ♪

06:33.743 --> 06:38.045
This hunk of junk. Your
sister buys stupid cars!

06:38.081 --> 06:40.982
Whoa! African candy.

06:42.152 --> 06:44.385
You know the car's not
from Africa, right, buddy?

06:44.421 --> 06:46.387
What's that?

06:46.423 --> 06:47.989
So, what's the brain plan, Dad?

06:48.024 --> 06:49.524
Well, I got to be honest, Jimmy.

06:49.559 --> 06:50.992
The brain plan is not a thing.

06:51.027 --> 06:52.527
Lots of things are changing,

06:52.562 --> 06:54.295
and we're just gonna play it out.

06:54.330 --> 06:56.564
After my friend Jason's
parents got divorced,

06:56.599 --> 06:58.166
his dad got a sweet new condo

06:58.201 --> 07:00.034
with a tennis court and a rec room,

07:00.069 --> 07:03.037
and there were airline pilots that
lived in the building, Dad.

07:03.072 --> 07:04.539
- Yeah?
- Yeah!

07:04.574 --> 07:05.973
Yeah, I mean, divorce sucks,

07:06.009 --> 07:07.175
but the one nice thing

07:07.210 --> 07:09.043
is you get a second
awesome place to live.

07:09.078 --> 07:10.378
You'd be okay with that?

07:10.413 --> 07:12.313
Are you kidding me? Of course I would.

07:12.348 --> 07:13.948
That means I'd have two houses.

07:13.983 --> 07:15.343
- [Chuckles]
- That's two kitchens.

07:15.351 --> 07:16.417
Two beds.

07:16.453 --> 07:18.453
Two bottles of ketchup!

07:18.488 --> 07:20.621
[Laughs]

07:20.657 --> 07:22.657
Hey, you know what, buddy?

07:22.692 --> 07:24.592
We're looking for apartments today.

07:24.627 --> 07:26.861
- Huh? Huh?
- Yes! Sweet! Cool!

07:26.896 --> 07:30.431
Wait, no. What about, uh,
Mom's plan to return the car?

07:30.467 --> 07:31.766
Plans?

07:31.801 --> 07:35.670
Where we're going, we
don't need... plans.

07:35.705 --> 07:38.439
[Gear grinds]

07:38.475 --> 07:40.908
Although we might need a tow truck.

07:40.944 --> 07:44.078
<i>No matter what my mom
says, I have to come out to Mimi.</i>

07:44.113 --> 07:45.980
<i>I just hope it goes okay.</i>

07:46.015 --> 07:48.416
<i>Hey, maybe we'll even end
up being best friends,</i>

07:48.451 --> 07:49.617
<i>like "Will & Grace."</i>

07:49.652 --> 07:51.219
[Cheers and applause]

07:53.890 --> 07:56.257
Hey, fella. Have a seat.

07:56.292 --> 07:58.726
Crowd: Oooh!

07:58.761 --> 08:02.296
Mimi, I have something to tell you.

08:02.332 --> 08:05.099
Now... it might not be easy to hear,

08:05.134 --> 08:08.202
and I'm sorry I didn't
tell you sooner, but...

08:08.238 --> 08:09.871
I'm gay.

08:09.906 --> 08:12.139
You're not gay.

08:12.175 --> 08:13.474
You're really gay.

08:13.510 --> 08:15.076
And now you can be my GBFF.

08:15.111 --> 08:17.945
[Applause]

08:17.981 --> 08:20.448
♪ ♪

08:20.483 --> 08:21.249
You're what?!

08:21.284 --> 08:22.284
I know. I'm sorry.

08:22.318 --> 08:23.584
I should have told you a long time ago,

08:23.620 --> 08:25.553
but, you know, I was still
trying to figure it out.

08:25.588 --> 08:26.988
This totally screws up my plan.

08:27.023 --> 08:28.656
Uh, your plan?

08:28.691 --> 08:30.725
I was going to lose my virginity to you.

08:30.760 --> 08:32.426
You checked off all the boxes...

08:32.462 --> 08:35.496
Smart, safe, good-looking enough.

08:35.532 --> 08:38.633
I put months into
grooming you to be the one,

08:38.668 --> 08:40.534
and now I have to start all over?

08:40.570 --> 08:42.803
I guess this explains
your stupid blouse.

08:42.839 --> 08:45.439
What? No. It's just a regular shirt!

08:45.475 --> 08:46.941
No, it's not!

08:46.976 --> 08:50.278
Thank you. Yes!

08:50.313 --> 08:52.246
I got your ham salad.

08:52.282 --> 08:53.948
I just picked it up off the porch.

08:53.983 --> 08:55.783
You could have come in and said hello.

08:55.818 --> 08:57.151
We're fine.

08:57.186 --> 08:58.653
Can't wait to see you
at the science fair.

08:58.688 --> 08:59.820
- [Doorbell rings]
- Woman: Oh. Sounds good.

08:59.856 --> 09:01.422
Uh, talk to you later. Okay.

09:01.457 --> 09:03.024
[Beep]

09:03.059 --> 09:04.759
[Sighs]

09:07.630 --> 09:09.030
- Another ham?
- [Tires squeal]

09:09.065 --> 09:10.831
We're fine!

09:12.201 --> 09:14.035
Oh, and you made me go as Justin Bieber

09:14.070 --> 09:16.203
for Halloween while you
got to be Selena Gomez!

09:16.239 --> 09:17.972
I mean, like, we won
a prize. Stop bitching.

09:18.007 --> 09:19.273
You don't get to be mad, Kenny!

09:19.309 --> 09:20.274
I'm the one who gets to be mad!

09:20.310 --> 09:21.342
Mimi!

09:21.377 --> 09:23.277
Aah!

09:23.313 --> 09:25.546
Why is there ham salad on the stairs?

09:30.438 --> 09:32.872
Do you hear that clicking?

09:32.908 --> 09:35.475
[Sighs] Don't be silly.

09:35.510 --> 09:37.544
I bet you're happy to see me go.

09:37.579 --> 09:39.679
I know you never really liked me.

09:39.714 --> 09:41.281
Oh, why would you say that?

09:41.316 --> 09:44.117
Because you said to my face
that you never really liked me.

09:44.152 --> 09:46.386
[Chuckling] I was just playing.

09:46.421 --> 09:48.354
You said, "I never really liked you.

09:48.390 --> 09:49.489
And I'm not playing."

09:49.524 --> 09:51.558
My, isn't memory a funny thing?

09:51.593 --> 09:54.961
Did you know Kenny was
gay before he told you?

09:54.996 --> 09:56.696
No.

09:56.731 --> 09:57.764
Did you?

09:59.167 --> 10:01.201
Ugh, I have cramps.

10:01.236 --> 10:03.336
Can I give you one of my teas?

10:05.040 --> 10:09.175
Mimi! Do these capris make me look fat?

10:09.211 --> 10:11.277
[Both chuckle]

10:11.313 --> 10:13.813
Your boobs feel squishy.

10:13.848 --> 10:16.849
I am such an idiot.

10:16.885 --> 10:18.384
This place is amazing.

10:18.420 --> 10:19.586
What?!

10:19.621 --> 10:22.288
It comes with a microwave.

10:22.324 --> 10:23.122
[Chuckles]

10:23.158 --> 10:24.557
And a bathroom! Dude.

10:24.593 --> 10:25.725
[Laughs] You see?

10:25.760 --> 10:27.894
We didn't have a plan,
and look what we found.

10:27.929 --> 10:28.995
Huh?

10:29.030 --> 10:30.830
Ah, this is working out great.

10:30.865 --> 10:32.665
So, what were you
thinking? Six-month lease?

10:32.701 --> 10:33.701
A year?

10:33.735 --> 10:35.068
Mm... I don't know.

10:35.103 --> 10:36.836
We're not really planning
things these days.

10:36.871 --> 10:39.205
There's a bed on the wall.

10:39.241 --> 10:41.341
And a jacuzzi in the rec room.

10:41.376 --> 10:42.809
Oh, my god.

10:42.844 --> 10:45.245
Dad, you have to get this place.

10:45.280 --> 10:47.814
Mom's never let us go in a jacuzzi.

10:47.849 --> 10:49.682
She calls it the devil's chowder.

10:49.718 --> 10:50.758
- [Chuckles]
- That's right.

10:50.785 --> 10:53.086
It's 'cause of the nudity and bacteria.

10:53.121 --> 10:55.288
But that doesn't scare us.

10:55.323 --> 10:57.390
- [Knocking]
- Oh.

10:57.425 --> 11:00.660
♪ ♪

11:02.430 --> 11:04.430
[Door opens]

11:04.466 --> 11:05.265
Hey.

11:05.300 --> 11:07.867
Hey. How you doing...

11:07.902 --> 11:10.069
Ohh... sport?

11:10.105 --> 11:12.605
Look, Kenny, I don't
want to be mad at you.

11:12.641 --> 11:15.508
Me neither. Come here, Biebs.

11:17.979 --> 11:20.246
- And I was thinking...
- Mm.

11:20.282 --> 11:22.382
Even if you are gay,

11:22.417 --> 11:23.483
that doesn't mean we still can't

11:23.518 --> 11:25.151
lose our virginity to each other.

11:25.186 --> 11:26.953
Doesn't it, though?

11:26.988 --> 11:28.054
We're such good friends,

11:28.089 --> 11:30.657
and I feel safe with you.

11:30.692 --> 11:32.392
Do you really want to go your whole life

11:32.427 --> 11:33.826
without knowing what it's like?

11:33.862 --> 11:38.031
Shouldn't you have something
to compare everything else to?

11:38.066 --> 11:40.199
<i>Maybe she's right.</i>

11:40.235 --> 11:42.502
<i>Shouldn't I know what it's like?</i>

11:42.537 --> 11:45.004
<i>Oh, this isn't so bad.</i>

11:45.040 --> 11:46.439
<i>And plus, if you squint,</i>

11:46.474 --> 11:49.242
<i>she looks a little like Orlando Bloom.</i>

11:52.414 --> 11:55.515
You won't be sorry.

